deck: King Lycaon was a king of Arcadia, who was turned into a wolf by Zeus.
description:
Mythology

In mythology King Lycaon was a king of Arcadia who sired 50 sons. Lycaon wanted to test if Zeus was omniscient so he chopped up a guest as an offering. Since poor hosting and murder were looked down upon in Greek society Zeus cursed Lyacon to turn into a wolf and struck down his 50 sons with lightning bolts. Lycaon's son Nyctimus survived Zeus' wrath.

This is where the term Lycanthropy came from to describe a werewolf.
name: Lycaon

description:
Origin

Joined the Genoshan Magistrates to help enforce the law of subverting mutants into slaves.

Creation

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by Marc Silvestri.

Major Story Arcs

While arresting Minister Ransome's family (he had helped his daughter Jennifer Ransome escape when he learned she had tested positive for being a mutant), Jan sees a boy protesting the magistrates's actions and decides to teach him a lesson. He attempts to beat the boy but gets stopped before any blows land. The boy is Phillip Moreau and he is the Genegineer's son. Jan realizes his mistake and immediately tries to brush the incident under the rug with some petty bribes. He is seemingly off the hook when Phillip runs away.
name: Jan

deck: Genoshan mutate with powers to heal the earth.
description:
Origin

While he used to be a normal citizen of Genosha, 7781 tested positive for the mutant gene and became a mutate to serve his country.

Creation

Written by Chris Claremont and drawn by Marc Silvestri.

Major Story Arcs

7781 seems to work directly for the Genegineer as an assistant in the garden. His powers are pretty extraordinary, as he is able to quickly heal a piece of scorched ground after some Magistrates land a ship in the Genegineer's yard.

deck: Enemy of the Secret Squadron and father of Fury Shark.
description:
Origin

A character called The Shark appeared in Captain Midnight 33 during his Fawcett run in the 1940s.

Ivan Shark was Hitler's top technology developer and a high ranking officer of the Nazis. He even knew some of Hitler's key plans. In a battle against the Secret Squadron, Ivan was accidentally knocked off the castle's wall by Captain Midnight. Having survived the fall by landing on soft snow, Ivan's head was ripped off by an angry polar bear.

He is survived by his daughter, Fury Shark.

issue_credits.name: On the Run, Part Two of Three

name: Ivan Shark
